This paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning (RL) agents to fulfill human preferences, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves training neural networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on human preferences suggests a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of RL agents also has applications in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
